VALUES
(42, 9, 47, 40, 19, 13, 15, NULL, 'Children and the Kingdom of Heaven', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' emphasis on children as exemplars of the kingdom of heaven. Both passages illustrate Jesus'' welcoming attitude towards children, demonstrating their importance in his teachings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 47, 43, 2, 25, 25, 'perceiving the thought of their heart', 'Understanding Human Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ability to perceive the thoughts of individuals. In Luke, He perceives the thoughts of the disciples, while in John, it states He knew what was in man.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 42, 14, 11, 11, 'he that is least among you all', 'Humility and Greatness', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility in both passages. Luke 9:48 emphasizes that the least among you shall be great, while Luke 14:11 states that those who humble themselves will be exalted.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 60, 5, 6, 6, 'he that is least among you all', 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility and the promise of exaltation. Luke 9:48 highlights that the least will be great, while 1 Peter 5:6 encourages believers to humble themselves for future exaltation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 40, 10, 40, 42, 'whosoever shall receive me', 'Connection of Reception and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving others in the name of Jesus, linking the act of hospitality to receiving divine rewards. They highlight that receiving the least or a righteous person carries significant spiritual implications.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 41, 9, 37, 37, NULL, 'Connection of Receiving Children', 'Both passages emphasize the act of receiving children in Jesus'' name as a means of receiving Him and the one who sent Him. This connection highlights the importance of humility and the value of the least among believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 42, 22, 26, 26, 'he that is least among you all', 'Greatness through Humility', 'Both passages emphasize the value of humility and service. Luke 9:48 highlights that the least among you shall be great, while Luke 22:26 teaches that the greatest must serve like the younger. This connection highlights the theme of true greatness in the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 43, 13, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Receiving and Sending', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between receiving individuals and receiving Jesus. They highlight that receiving those sent by Jesus equates to receiving Him and, by extension, the one who sent Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 48, 40, 23, 11, 12, 'he that is least among you all', 'Servanthood and Humility', 'Both passages emphasize the value of humility and servanthood. Luke highlights that the least among you shall be great, while Matthew states that the greatest shall be your servant.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 41, 9, 38, 40, 'casting out devils in thy name', 'Connection of Casting Out Devils', 'Both passages emphasize the act of casting out devils in Jesus'' name. They highlight the disciples'' concern about someone not following them, yet Jesus teaches inclusivity in ministry.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 4, 11, 27, 29, 'forbad him', 'Authority and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forbidding others from exercising spiritual authority. In Luke, John forbids someone casting out devils, while in Numbers, Joshua wants to stop Eldad and Medad from prophesying. This connection highlights the tension between exclusivity and inclusivity in spiritual practices.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 41, 10, 13, 14, 'forbad him, because he followeth not with us', 'Rebuking Others in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of forbidding others from ministering in Jesus'' name. Both passages emphasize the disciples'' tendency to restrict access to Jesus, whether it be casting out devils or bringing children to Him.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 44, 4, 18, 19, 'in thy name', 'Authority in Jesus'' Name', 'Both passages emphasize the use of Jesus'' name in ministry. In Luke, John expresses concern over someone casting out devils in Jesus'' name, while in Acts, Peter and John assert their right to teach in that same name despite opposition.', 'theme', 0.286, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 44, 5, 28, 28, 'in thy name', 'Authority in Teaching and Healing', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority in performing acts in Jesus'' name. Both passages emphasize the response to those who teach or act without being part of the established group.', 'theme', 0.286, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 42, 5, 5, 5, NULL, 'Authority and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to Jesus'' authority. In both passages, the characters respond to Jesus'' command, whether in casting out devils or letting down the net.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 49, 52, 2, 16, 16, 'forbad him', 'Forbidding and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of forbidding others from acting in accordance with God''s will. Both passages emphasize the act of preventing others from sharing or spreading the message of salvation.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 40, 12, 30, 30, 'not against us is for us', 'Inclusion and Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of alignment with Jesus. Luke 9:50 suggests that those not opposing are supportive, while Matthew 12:30 states that lack of support equates to opposition.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 42, 11, 23, 23, NULL, 'Contrasting Views on Allegiance', 'This connection highlights the differing perspectives on allegiance to Jesus. In Luke 9:50, the idea is that those not opposing Jesus are considered allies, while Luke 11:23 emphasizes a more definitive stance, stating that those not actively supporting Him are against Him.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 46, 12, 3, 3, 'for he that is not against us', 'Unity in the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among believers. Both passages emphasize that those who acknowledge Jesus are aligned with Him, whether they are explicitly part of the group or not.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 50, 1, 15, 18, 'he that is not against us is for us', 'Unity in Preaching Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity in the preaching of Christ. Both passages emphasize that those who proclaim Christ, regardless of their motives, are not against the gospel.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 42, 16, 13, 13, 'for he that is not against us', 'Service and Loyalty to God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of allegiance. In Luke 9:50, Jesus indicates that those who are not against Him are on His side, while Luke 16:13 highlights the impossibility of serving two masters, underscoring the necessity of loyalty to God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 20, 3, 5, 6, NULL, 'Trust and Support in God', 'This connection highlights the importance of trust and support in one''s faith journey. Both passages emphasize reliance on God rather than one''s own understanding or judgment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 50, 41, 9, 41, 41, 'for us', 'Unity in Service to Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusivity in service to Christ. Both passages emphasize that acts done in His name, whether large or small, are valued and rewarded.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 23, 50, 5, 9, 'stedfastly set his face', 'Determination in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of steadfastness in the face of suffering. Luke''s ''stedfastly set his face'' parallels Isaiah''s ''set my face like a flint,'' highlighting a resolute commitment to their respective paths despite impending challenges.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 41, 16, 19, 19, 'received up', 'Journey to Divine Ascension', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' journey culminating in his ascension. In Luke 9:51, Jesus ''stedfastly set his face to go to Jerusalem,'' indicating his determination to fulfill his mission, which leads to his being ''received up into heaven'' in Mark 16:19.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 42, 18, 31, 31, 'go to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem, highlighting its significance in the narrative. In Luke 9:51, Jesus ''stedfastly set his face to go to Jerusalem,'' while in Luke 18:31, he explicitly states, ''we go up to Jerusalem.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 42, 13, 22, 22, NULL, 'Journey Toward Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem, highlighting Jesus'' determination and purpose. The phrase ''journeying toward Jerusalem'' in the target passage reflects the steadfastness noted in the source passage.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 12, 2, 1, 3, 'the time was come that he should be received up', 'Journey to Divine Ascension', 'Both passages emphasize a significant journey towards a divine event. In Luke, Jesus sets his face to go to Jerusalem, while Elijah travels with Elisha towards his ascension into heaven.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 12, 2, 11, 11, 'he should be received up', 'Ascension and Divine Journey', 'Both passages emphasize a significant ascent, with Luke highlighting Jesus'' steadfast journey to Jerusalem and 2 Kings describing Elijah''s dramatic ascent into heaven. This connection highlights the theme of divine elevation and purpose in their respective narratives.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 51, 43, 6, 62, 62, NULL, 'Ascension of the Son of Man', 'This connection highlights the theme of ascension in both passages. Luke 9:51 mentions Jesus setting his face to go to Jerusalem, indicating a journey towards his eventual ascension, while John 6:62 directly references the Son of Man ascending to where he was before.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
